## Batch 1: Resume Templates

### 1a. Chronological Resume
Use the gold_template_builder skill.

Design a "Chronological" resume template for Australian community services roles.

Requirements:
- Section order: Contact Block → Target Role Title ({{TARGET_ROLE}}) → Professional Summary → Skills (skills grid) → Professional Experience (reverse chronological) → Education → Certifications
- Contact Block MUST use line breaks instead of pipe (|) characters for separation to ensure ATS compliance.
- Certifications MUST be the final section.
- Use PLACEHOLDER_SCHEMA_V2 tokens for `resume` type.
- Target 6 roles × 4 bullets each (ROLE_1 through ROLE_6).
- 6 skills slots (SKILL_1 through SKILL_6).
- Heading hierarchy: Name as Title, sections as Heading 1, role titles as Heading 2. Must use native Google Docs style tags (no manual bold for headings).
- Typography: Calibri 11pt body, Calibri 14pt headings, 1.15 line spacing, 6pt spacing after paragraphs.
- Glyphs: Only standard hyphens (-) or standard circular bullets. Strictly NO custom bullet characters (•, ✔, ★, ❖, ●, ✅, ❌, |).
- ATS audit against ats_rules.json.
- Output the doc_templates.json registration fragment for resume.variants.chronological.
- Output the dry-run command.

### 1b. Hybrid Resume
Use the gold_template_builder skill.

Design a "Hybrid" (functional + chronological) resume template.

Requirements:
- Section order: Contact Block → Target Role Title ({{TARGET_ROLE}}) → Professional/Strengths Summary → Skills (top 6 skills, drawn from {{SKILL_1}} to {{SKILL_6}}) → Professional Experience (abbreviated chronological list: title/org/dates using {{ROLE_N_TITLE}}, {{ROLE_N_ORG}}, and {{ROLE_N_DATES}}, with no per-role bullets to keep the layout condensed) → Education → Certifications
- Contact Block MUST use line breaks instead of pipe (|) characters.
- Built specifically for career-transition candidates: the Skills section MUST use Rosetta Stone community framing to translate and reframe corporate finance expertise into community service assets.
- Abbreviate actual experience to a flat chronological list of organization, role title, and dates to keep focus entirely on skills and competencies.
- Same ATS rules, same typography (Calibri 11pt, 1.15 spacing, 6pt after), same placeholder schema, standard hyphens/circular bullets only.
- Output the doc_templates.json registration fragment for resume.variants.hybrid.
- Output the dry-run command.

